The paper deals with statistical query algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses memory and communication constraints, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithmic approaches and their power suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
